  <div class="row" id="query11-div">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/query11">Query 1.1 [Net Balance Over a Time Period]</a>
      <p>The purpose of this query is to check the “balance” or the movement of money of a 
        single account by subtracting the sum of all the debit labeled transactions 
        from the sum of all the credit labeled transactions. Since the start date and 
        end date of the transactions is also available, whoever is querying also has the 
        ability to check transactions between two dates such as a certain month or a week.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Query 1.2 -->
  <br><br>
  <div class="row" id="query12-div">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/query12">Query 1.2 [Characterization Summary of Transactions]</a>
      <p>The purpose of this query is to show the general information about all the transactions 
        of a certain characterization (such as credited interest or insurance payment) per 
        account, like the total amount per account or number of transactions per account. 
        The transactions queried can also be between two specified dates so the user can 
        check transactions for a certain month or week.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr>
  <!-- Query 2.1 -->
  <br><br>
  <img src="../img/query2-img.png" height="200px" class="mx-auto d-block">
  <br>

  <div class="row" id="Count of Credit Card Holders of a Type and Disposition">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/query21">Query 2.1 [Count of Credit Card Holders of a Type and Disposition]</a>
      <p>The purpose of this query is to get the total number of card type per disposition 
        type, that is, the query makes use of the Card and Disposition tables to obtain 
        the number of clients who own the following type of cards offered by the Czech 
        bank: Gold, classic, and junior.  Each client, or disposition type, is distinguished 
        by two categories: If they are an owner or a disponent, or someone who uses or is 
        in charge of the card type reflected in the table but does not own it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Query 2.2 -->
  <br><br>
  <div class="row" id="Status of Loans and Remaining Balance to be Paid by a Customer">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/query22">Query 2.2 [Header]</a>
      <p>The purpose of this query is to show if the selected account has any loans. 
        If the account has a loan in record, the details will be displayed. 
        The loan ID, the date the loan was taken, and its current status will be 
        displayed. If the loan is not yet fully paid the remaining balance will be 
        shown by subtracting the transactions made to the loan taken, otherwise it 
        will display that the loan is finished.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

