  <div class="row" id="query31-div">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/query31">Query 3.1 [Total Value of Permanent Orders of a Payment Type per District]</a>
      <p>The purpose of this query is to check the total amount gained by a district
         using a particular characterization method that determines the nature of 
         the payment. This enables the user to see which method or characterization 
         has the most amount and is most frequent in a district and could help 
         determine the status of which transaction is most apparent in a district.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Query 3.2 -->
  <br><br>
  <div class="row" id="query32-div">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/query32">Query 3.2 [Summary of Transactions of a Payment Type in a Certain Timespan per District]</a>
      <p>The purpose of this query is to show the users, how many transactions and the 
        total amount of transactions are made per district of a certain characterization 
        of transaction (K_Symbol) in a timespan . In the real world, this is an important 
        feature because it enables the users (banks) to see in what district do they have 
        the most  transactions of a certain K_symbol so they can upgrade their services 
        based on the data available. It also enables them to see how many people use their 
        bank in a specific time period so they can analyze how their bank is doing.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

