  <div class="row" id="query41-div">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/query41">Query 4.1 [Transaction Activity of Specific Types of Credit Card Holders based on District Purpose]</a>
      <p>Credit Card Holders represent a portion of the bank’s customer base that is a constant 
        source of revenue through interest payments. Knowing the transaction activity of credit 
        card holders in a certain district would allow the bank to formulate business strategies 
        that would take advantage of the holders’ activities, such as providing better interest 
        rates and promos for credit card applications in districts with low activity in order 
        entice residents there to get credit cards. In districts with large activity, the bank 
        can focus collection efforts in those districts to increase the likelihood that high 
        value credit card loans are paid for. 
        <br>
        <br>
	      Also, knowing which type of credit card holder is active in a district informs decisions 
        on prestige offers for gold holders, who are large spenders, to entice them to spend/transact 
        with the bank more and go through the bank using their credit cards. In districts with 
        low gold/classic spending, efforts can be made to make higher tier credit cards be more 
        desirable.
        <br>
        <br>
	      Ultimately, the information informs business decisions regarding tiered credit cards and 
        prestige offers, and to which districts these efforts are directed to.
</p>
    </div>
  </div>

